      passage: `The following text is adapted from Henry James's 1881 novel <i>The Portrait of a Lady</i>.<br><br>Everything Osmond did was pose—pose so subtly considered that if one were not on the lookout one mistook it for impulse. Ralph had never met a man who lived so much in the land of consideration. His tastes, his studies, his accomplishments, his collections, were all for a purpose.`,
